As I reached for the doorknob, I remembered the first time I saw her. Her long, silky, chestnut hair hung gracefully to her waist, and her big, dark eyes matched her wide, welcoming smile. I had fallen in love with her the moment she opened the door, but she had never noticed me. I could only watch from afar as she began her senior year at NCSU, and then moved on to the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill. I waited patiently for three years, and then, finally, she graduated from UNC with a bachelor’s degree in Psychology. My love for her had grown steadily since the day I first saw her, and I could wait no longer. I knew it was time to make my move. My hand shook as I reached for the phone. My heart raced as I dialed her number. I was nervous, but I knew I had to tell her. She picked up the phone, and I began to speak. “I’ve loved you since the first time I saw you,” I told her. “I’ve waited for three years, and now I’m finally ready to ask you to be my girlfriend.” I held my breath as I waited for her response. She was silent for a moment, and then she told me, “I’ve always loved you too.” I was elated! I had waited for this moment for so long, and now it was finally here. I told her that I would call her again the next day. I hung up the phone and smiled to myself. I knew I had to do something special to make this day even more memorable. I grabbed my camera and headed to the mailbox. I had an idea. I had been sending her postcards for months, and now I had an idea for the perfect postcard. I snapped a picture of the mailbox, and then
